getAdmissibleDistanceBounds

public final Bounds getAdmissibleDistanceBounds(TimePoint tpFrom,
                                                TimePoint tpTo)
Gets the minimum and maximum allowed distance between a pair of TimePoints.

Parameters:
tpFrom - the TimePoint that is considered as the "origin"/source.
tpTo - the TimePoint that is considered as the "target".
Returns:
Returns the bounds of the distance between the two TimePoints or null if there is no constraint between the two.

getAdmissibleDistanceBounds

public final Bounds getAdmissibleDistanceBounds(TimePoint tpTo)
Get the minimum and maximum allowed distance between the global source and a TimePoint. Calling this function is equivalent to calling getAdmissibleDistanceBounds(TimePoint, TimePoint) With the parameters (Source, tpTo).

Parameters:
tpTo - the TimePoint whose temporal placement should be queried.
Returns:
The allowed bounds of the TimePoint.
